The paper discusses access patterns in object-oriented or object-relational databases, which are typically studied in the context of database systems (cs.DB). The paper proposes a framework for evaluating dynamic object access patterns, which involves techniques for information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also evaluates the performance of dynamic clustering algorithms, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper mentions multimedia databases, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the storage and retrieval of multimedia content (cs.MM).
